{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/on-design-systems-3/","webpackCompilationHash":"89d141fdc6a01acd0df6","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":":heart: React","author":"Metamn"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"a156f02c-2e7c-5b7a-9701-c4c43bf1b9e9","excerpt":"Consistent user interfaces in web context.","html":"<p>Consistent user interfaces in web context.</p>\n<!--more-->\n<hr>\n<h2>Consistent user interfaces</h2>\n<p>Consistent — coherent and uniform — user interfaces display no visual and logical glitches.</p>\n<p>User interfaces, when consistent, <em>feel</em> complete. They have no visible errors, and the experience they provide resembles enjoying an artwork.</p>\n<p>Consistent, <a href=\"https://www.wordnik.com/words/consistent\">by definition</a>, is in agreement with itself. It holds true as a group, it’s not contradictory. It’s marked by an orderly, logical, and aesthetically consistent relation of parts. It’s unity and harmony.</p>\n<p>Consistent UIs talk about the intent and the mastery of its creators. They persuade. They deliver an important message.</p>\n<h2>The current landscape</h2>\n<p>Until recent years, creating — designing and developing — consistent user interfaces were a herculean task.</p>\n<p>With <a href=\"http://metamn.io/react/on-design-systems-2/\">design systems thinking</a> — by introducing a novel design process — now consitent <em>design</em> is possible.</p>\n<p>The question is still open for the implementation part. Is consistent implementation possible?</p>\n<p>The design / development separation exists because current UX/UI design tools and processes, even following the design systems paradigm, produce visual deliverables. Artifacts requiring further translation to a computing platform via code.</p>\n<p>This article examines the web platform. How to develop consistent UIs with web technologies?</p>\n<h2>The web context</h2>\n<p>The web platform — we all know well — is the browser.</p>\n<p>By using technologies like HTML, CSS, and Javascript — it manages to display interactive information across different devices and operating systems.</p>\n<p>Developing consistent UIs in web context, thus, translates into implementing a design system with HTML, CSS, and Javascript — and running it in the browser.</p>\n<h2>The historical context</h2>\n<p>Web front-end development has a long history. Through decades, it evolved from one paradigm to another.</p>\n<p>Let’s put design systems into this historical context.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/d455e1263037f662051560e7d9e36ccc/839e9/ds-context-black-nologo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 112.71769947347103%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The context\"\n        title=\"The context\"\n        src=\"/react/static/d455e1263037f662051560e7d9e36ccc/5cc77/ds-context-black-nologo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/d455e1263037f662051560e7d9e36ccc/72cd8/ds-context-black-nologo.png 192w,\n/react/static/d455e1263037f662051560e7d9e36ccc/45483/ds-context-black-nologo.png 384w,\n/react/static/d455e1263037f662051560e7d9e36ccc/5cc77/ds-context-black-nologo.png 768w,\n/react/static/d455e1263037f662051560e7d9e36ccc/04090/ds-context-black-nologo.png 1152w,\n/react/static/d455e1263037f662051560e7d9e36ccc/ccc27/ds-context-black-nologo.png 1536w,\n/react/static/d455e1263037f662051560e7d9e36ccc/839e9/ds-context-black-nologo.png 2469w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Each quadrant represents an era in web development; the historical timeline reads counter-clockwise; the axes connect web development to general software development practice: APIs and frameworks.</p>\n<p>And the story, in short, follows.</p>\n<p>In the beginning — <strong>Classless HTML</strong> — there wasn’t much styling and interactivity on websites. HTML was not linked to CSS and Javascript via class names — hence the name.</p>\n<p><strong>CSS Frameworks</strong> are the longest reigning paradigm. They are ubiquitous. Perhaps they are responsible for styling 90% or more of all webpages today. CSS frameworks are all household names: Bootstrap, Foundation, Tachyons, Bulma, Tailwind.</p>\n<p><strong>Component libraries</strong> and <strong>design systems</strong> are new. The line between them is blurry — for the novice — but important in making a UI consistent or not.</p>\n<h2>The journey</h2>\n<p>It takes a journey from the term <code class=\"language-text\">user interface</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">consistent web user interface</code>.</p>\n<p>For those on the run, there is a big picture. It’s enjoyable on larger screens via a click.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/d8a803ed8c0da163804a4c461c782264/53472/uniform-ui.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 15.085158150851582%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAYAAACTWi8uAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAa0lEQVQI1zVO2wpAIQzq/3+0h4puRBHVDspxIG1Oc87+WmvZnNNKKRZjtL03ebytNe7HGNZ7t3svd+89cvCpHAQwhBCIWivnnDPNmAEFpZQI+bz35KVz5xwDJJAZqbgAl2GnDwEEQysevfABMgvnJSeIRLgAAAAASUVORK5CYII='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Uniform UI\"\n        title=\"Uniform UI\"\n        src=\"/react/static/d8a803ed8c0da163804a4c461c782264/5cc77/uniform-ui.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/d8a803ed8c0da163804a4c461c782264/72cd8/uniform-ui.png 192w,\n/react/static/d8a803ed8c0da163804a4c461c782264/45483/uniform-ui.png 384w,\n/react/static/d8a803ed8c0da163804a4c461c782264/5cc77/uniform-ui.png 768w,\n/react/static/d8a803ed8c0da163804a4c461c782264/04090/uniform-ui.png 1152w,\n/react/static/d8a803ed8c0da163804a4c461c782264/ccc27/uniform-ui.png 1536w,\n/react/static/d8a803ed8c0da163804a4c461c782264/53472/uniform-ui.png 1644w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>For the rest, there is a breakdown. A step-by-step guide where at the end a consistent UI approach unfolds.</p>\n<h2>User interfaces</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/06cdc3d407cc88d2144b557ac36f0900/922ae/ui1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.347826086956516%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"UI\"\n        title=\"UI\"\n        src=\"/react/static/06cdc3d407cc88d2144b557ac36f0900/5cc77/ui1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/06cdc3d407cc88d2144b557ac36f0900/72cd8/ui1.png 192w,\n/react/static/06cdc3d407cc88d2144b557ac36f0900/45483/ui1.png 384w,\n/react/static/06cdc3d407cc88d2144b557ac36f0900/5cc77/ui1.png 768w,\n/react/static/06cdc3d407cc88d2144b557ac36f0900/922ae/ui1.png 874w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>User interfaces display information. Information equipped with structure, presentation and behaviour.</p>\n<p>Structure and presentation is familiar from graphic and print design. It defines layout and style.</p>\n<p>Behaviour is specific to interactive environments like the web. This dynamic context requires the user interface to handle change — to behave on change.\nPer se, it equips information with a dynamic attribute.</p>\n<h2>Web user interfaces</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/27774e204741fb9e37b09650216bae56/71a9e/ui2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 70.87599544937429%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Web UI\"\n        title=\"Web UI\"\n        src=\"/react/static/27774e204741fb9e37b09650216bae56/5cc77/ui2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/27774e204741fb9e37b09650216bae56/72cd8/ui2.png 192w,\n/react/static/27774e204741fb9e37b09650216bae56/45483/ui2.png 384w,\n/react/static/27774e204741fb9e37b09650216bae56/5cc77/ui2.png 768w,\n/react/static/27774e204741fb9e37b09650216bae56/71a9e/ui2.png 879w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Web user interfaces rely on a specific technology — the browser — to display information.</p>\n<p>Browsers:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Structure information with <strong>HTML</strong>.</li>\n<li>Define style via <strong>CSS</strong>.</li>\n<li>Handle behaviour using <strong>Javascript</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Binding</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/eb16f3df4b64065d57192e866a013549/386eb/ui3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.40229885057471%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Binding\"\n        title=\"Binding\"\n        src=\"/react/static/eb16f3df4b64065d57192e866a013549/5cc77/ui3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/eb16f3df4b64065d57192e866a013549/72cd8/ui3.png 192w,\n/react/static/eb16f3df4b64065d57192e866a013549/45483/ui3.png 384w,\n/react/static/eb16f3df4b64065d57192e866a013549/5cc77/ui3.png 768w,\n/react/static/eb16f3df4b64065d57192e866a013549/386eb/ui3.png 870w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>HTML, CSS and Javascript are standalone technologies. To work together — they must merge, bind together.</p>\n<p>The way of binding — the binding methods — are important. Each method defines a paradigm, an era in front-end development.</p>\n<h4>Classless</h4>\n<p>This paradigm makes no explicit bounds between HTML, CSS and Javascript.</p>\n<p>HTML has no classes, thus styles and behaviour attached. Styling comes from a separate CSS file, behaviour comes from a separate JavaScript file, and everything binds together via naming conventions.</p>\n<p>Naming conventions are the last thing to scale.</p>\n<h4>Class-based binding</h4>\n<p>The next paradigm connects the separate parts — HTML, CSS, Javascript — via class names, a special HTML attribute.</p>\n<p>In spite of being the longest reigning paradigm — CSS frameworks — are <a href=\"https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/enduring-css/9781787282803/ch02.html\">fragile</a> in scaling, composition.</p>\n<h4>Props</h4>\n<p>The latest advancement specific for component libraries and design systems — integrate, bind natively all parts of the displayable information — structure, style, behaviour — into a single standalone component.</p>\n<p>Scaling and composition now relates to one single item — the component — vs. three items — HTML, CSS, and JavaScript — as it were before.</p>\n<h2>API</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/920a4dbbd93bd2e8755b7f49c2301323/27d9c/ui4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.53669724770643%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"API\"\n        title=\"API\"\n        src=\"/react/static/920a4dbbd93bd2e8755b7f49c2301323/5cc77/ui4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/920a4dbbd93bd2e8755b7f49c2301323/72cd8/ui4.png 192w,\n/react/static/920a4dbbd93bd2e8755b7f49c2301323/45483/ui4.png 384w,\n/react/static/920a4dbbd93bd2e8755b7f49c2301323/5cc77/ui4.png 768w,\n/react/static/920a4dbbd93bd2e8755b7f49c2301323/27d9c/ui4.png 872w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The acronym stands for Application Programming Interface and comes from general software development theory.</p>\n<p>APIs bind together standalone parts of a software system — in our case HTML, CSS and Javascript — in a programmable way.</p>\n<p>The higher the programmability of the bindings — based on API — the better the quality and scalability of the system.</p>\n<h2>Template- and Component-based UI frameworks</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/61a1f3a5f778e116935a76c8191f5e59/27d9c/ui5.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 14.3348623853211%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAYAAACTWi8uAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAb0lEQVQI1z2OWQoAIQxDvf8JPYH7jvrb4RWcQkjaplEz55QxhuLp3rsCvdaS1prce4VKKf0e/M8Laq1iSinivRc4hKCMMeesiDGqkSBrrYZTBLCnP+fobO8tBjMLgh4zg9+MMB7hl8451e8OJhTQfxLh40ptEwtNAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Template-based UI framework\"\n        title=\"Template-based UI framework\"\n        src=\"/react/static/61a1f3a5f778e116935a76c8191f5e59/5cc77/ui5.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/61a1f3a5f778e116935a76c8191f5e59/72cd8/ui5.png 192w,\n/react/static/61a1f3a5f778e116935a76c8191f5e59/45483/ui5.png 384w,\n/react/static/61a1f3a5f778e116935a76c8191f5e59/5cc77/ui5.png 768w,\n/react/static/61a1f3a5f778e116935a76c8191f5e59/27d9c/ui5.png 872w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/95089c54302daea7cb2b4c9d9f6f2011/27d9c/ui6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 29.357798165137616%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Component-based UI framework\"\n        title=\"Component-based UI framework\"\n        src=\"/react/static/95089c54302daea7cb2b4c9d9f6f2011/5cc77/ui6.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/95089c54302daea7cb2b4c9d9f6f2011/72cd8/ui6.png 192w,\n/react/static/95089c54302daea7cb2b4c9d9f6f2011/45483/ui6.png 384w,\n/react/static/95089c54302daea7cb2b4c9d9f6f2011/5cc77/ui6.png 768w,\n/react/static/95089c54302daea7cb2b4c9d9f6f2011/27d9c/ui6.png 872w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>Template-based UI frameworks</strong> use class names as an API mechanism to bind together HTML, CSS and Javascript.</p>\n<p>The binding is always open. An HTML element can take any number of CSS styles or JavaScript interaction handlers.</p>\n<p>This leads to an open API, where everything is possible, even chaotic user interfaces.</p>\n<p><strong>Component-based UI frameworks</strong> use props as an API mechanism to bind together components.</p>\n<p>Props-based binding gives a choice. Either go with an open, or a closed API.</p>\n<h2>Open and closed APIs</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/f57abfc6763a97d6f753d1b83f48cc63/922ae/ui7.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.58352402745996%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Open API\"\n        title=\"Open API\"\n        src=\"/react/static/f57abfc6763a97d6f753d1b83f48cc63/5cc77/ui7.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/f57abfc6763a97d6f753d1b83f48cc63/72cd8/ui7.png 192w,\n/react/static/f57abfc6763a97d6f753d1b83f48cc63/45483/ui7.png 384w,\n/react/static/f57abfc6763a97d6f753d1b83f48cc63/5cc77/ui7.png 768w,\n/react/static/f57abfc6763a97d6f753d1b83f48cc63/922ae/ui7.png 874w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/af85b43ac8c05a898bf1c59eaed626d2/47573/ui8.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 16.818181818181817%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAYAAACTWi8uAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAhklEQVQI11WPWwrFIAxE3f/yXIForfigtuIDoZrL5KNwA0PI5GREcd83oWqtdBwHee9ZIQT2n+dhSSkppURzTlJKMXNdF9845z5W5Jx5AIjQ1hr13mmMQXtvwh47dAS870ulFBY4dNyttZgRMUbSWvNL1tpPmI0x3BGMgg/vPM8/FkIGfvUDS2DjJiZ3cRkAAAAASUVORK5CYII='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Closed API\"\n        title=\"Closed API\"\n        src=\"/react/static/af85b43ac8c05a898bf1c59eaed626d2/5cc77/ui8.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/af85b43ac8c05a898bf1c59eaed626d2/72cd8/ui8.png 192w,\n/react/static/af85b43ac8c05a898bf1c59eaed626d2/45483/ui8.png 384w,\n/react/static/af85b43ac8c05a898bf1c59eaed626d2/5cc77/ui8.png 768w,\n/react/static/af85b43ac8c05a898bf1c59eaed626d2/47573/ui8.png 880w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In <strong>Open APIs</strong>, parts compose up freely without constraints. No rules offer unlimited room for experimentation and play.</p>\n<p>CSS frameworks — by their nature — and Component libraries — by choice — offer open APIs.</p>\n<p><strong>Closed APIs</strong> restrict the arbitrary composition of the parts with rules. Rules offer consistency and scalability.</p>\n<p>Classless HTML frameworks — by their nature — and design systems — by choice — embrace the closed API principle.</p>\n<h2>Consistent and non-consistent UIs</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/6b1776aff30f2e7cb87c25d422295c4b/47573/ui9a.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 16.818181818181817%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAYAAACTWi8uAAAACXBIWXMAAAsTAAALEwEAmpwYAAAAiUlEQVQI12WOWQ6EIBBEvf/1vIAKImAAN5SQYE2qE7+mk5feqpdu33e01qCUgrVWWJZF8ud5cJ4nqOn7Xnree6zrKhhjMM+z1I7jwLZt6GKMqLXiui6BDcIlpRSEEMRTzJhHcs7CN3Pft+xIKaGjkB/xinNO/Ac/Yu19X9C01hjHEdM0/TEMg2h/sZribJ1fyggAAAAASUVORK5CYII='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"CSS framework\"\n        title=\"CSS framework\"\n        src=\"/react/static/6b1776aff30f2e7cb87c25d422295c4b/5cc77/ui9a.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/6b1776aff30f2e7cb87c25d422295c4b/72cd8/ui9a.png 192w,\n/react/static/6b1776aff30f2e7cb87c25d422295c4b/45483/ui9a.png 384w,\n/react/static/6b1776aff30f2e7cb87c25d422295c4b/5cc77/ui9a.png 768w,\n/react/static/6b1776aff30f2e7cb87c25d422295c4b/47573/ui9a.png 880w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/acec4e914312fec2bbcfbbef64d49d87/47573/ui9.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 16.818181818181817%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAYAAACTWi8uAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAg0lEQVQI122PWQrEIBBEvf/1vIBbJComkk30wxpKmPzMNBSN3a8fKPZ9RykF67piWRZ475FSmu8QAnLOOI4DUso5izHOPUOWN5yRoUdQ2HvHdV04z3P253lw3/fMtm1orYEc5bXWd0f2y9NBRtCulIK1dsYY85MxBljOOWit/zJ08EcfTxjhfD4J5kMAAAAASUVORK5CYII='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Component library\"\n        title=\"Component library\"\n        src=\"/react/static/acec4e914312fec2bbcfbbef64d49d87/5cc77/ui9.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/acec4e914312fec2bbcfbbef64d49d87/72cd8/ui9.png 192w,\n/react/static/acec4e914312fec2bbcfbbef64d49d87/45483/ui9.png 384w,\n/react/static/acec4e914312fec2bbcfbbef64d49d87/5cc77/ui9.png 768w,\n/react/static/acec4e914312fec2bbcfbbef64d49d87/47573/ui9.png 880w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/462a0ba557c67dfd7ab9ddbed0f8e8c3/47573/ui10.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 16.818181818181817%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAYAAACTWi8uAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAhklEQVQI11WOWwrFIBBD3f/y3IBaC4oitdQnReeSgX7cAZkYjonivm/CnOdJx3HQdV3knOP7nJOe5yEwUkoKITDrvWcGfIyRUkrsgxMIWGtRrZVyzrwRgvO+L3tjDC7Cw703tdaolMIMdO+dfTACrUopbrPW8v60MYY1YAw8rfUf82lk4Oc//q3iZiubVX8AAAAASUVORK5CYII='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Design system\"\n        title=\"Design system\"\n        src=\"/react/static/462a0ba557c67dfd7ab9ddbed0f8e8c3/5cc77/ui10.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/462a0ba557c67dfd7ab9ddbed0f8e8c3/72cd8/ui10.png 192w,\n/react/static/462a0ba557c67dfd7ab9ddbed0f8e8c3/45483/ui10.png 384w,\n/react/static/462a0ba557c67dfd7ab9ddbed0f8e8c3/5cc77/ui10.png 768w,\n/react/static/462a0ba557c67dfd7ab9ddbed0f8e8c3/47573/ui10.png 880w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>API-type and framework-type — combined — defines if a paradigm will produce consistent user interfaces, or not.</p>\n<p><strong>CSS frameworks</strong> are Template-based UI frameworks with class-based API bindings resulting, involuntarily and by definition, in an open-ended API.</p>\n<p>Guaranteeing consistency in such an environment is possible, on a small scale, with considerable efforts.</p>\n<p><strong>Component libraries</strong> are Component-based UI frameworks with props-based API bindings who choose the open-ended approach.</p>\n<p>Guaranteeing consistency is possible, again, with restrictions and effort.</p>\n<p><strong>Design systems</strong> — Component-based UI frameworks — choose the constraints-based API approach to deliver consistency.</p>\n<h2>A new take</h2>\n<p>Creating consistent user interfaces in web context is possible.</p>\n<p>To achieve this feature, one should move away from hacking — binding with class names — to programming — binding with props.</p>\n<p>And to move from non-programming languages — HTML, CSS — to programming languages — components built on JSX, CSS-in-JS.</p>\n<p>Once everything is programmable, it becomes standard, classic software development.</p>\n<p>Where well-known, battle-tested theory and practice — API, Framework — apply, to solve consistency and scalability.</p>\n<h2>Resources</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.wordnik.com/words/consistent\">Consistent — Definitions</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://metamn.io/react/on-design-systems-2/\">On design systems — 2: Tools and processes</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/enduring-css/9781787282803/ch02.html\">The Problems of CSS at Scale</a></li>\n</ol>","frontmatter":{"title":"On design systems — 3","date":"November 22, 2021"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/on-design-systems-3/","previous":{"excerpt":"Design tools and processes.","fields":{"slug":"/on-design-systems-2/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"On design systems — 2"}},"next":{"excerpt":"A series of articles.","fields":{"slug":"/on-design-systems/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"On design systems"}}}}}